<p><b>What is the science behind blue eyes?</b> The more melanin in the eye, the darker your eye color will appear. But blue eyes don't have any blue pigment in them. Blue eyes get their color the same way water and the sky get their blue color. They scatter light so that more blue light reflects back out.</p>
